	quest.4D77214933327DFB.quest_desc: [
		"Oops! You've garnered yourself the &dWrath of the Hive&r, a condition which makes &aall nearby bees furious&r. They will attack you, and any non-bee creatures nearby."
		""
		"It turns out, &eBees&r don't like it when you steal their hard-earned &bHoney&r, or &aattempting to harm them&r. The following actions will anger the hive:"
		""
		"- Damaging any &eBee&r or their &eQueen&r."
		"- Breaking translucent &bHoney Blocks&r."
		"- Using Glass Bottles on &bFilled Porous Honeycomb blocks&r."
		"- Destroying a &bHoneycomb Brood Block&r without &aSilk Touch&r."
		"- Entering a &cCell Maze&r."
		""
		"How can you avoid this negative effect? Well, you can &aingratiate yourself to the hive&r by &6feeding sweets to &eBees&r. This will sometimes grant you &bProtection of the Hive&r, which will cause Bees to come to your aid in battle, and provides a &done time forgiveness&r when doing any of the above actions."
		""
		"- &bSugar Water Bottles&r have a 7% chance of granting &bProtection of the Hive&r."
		"- &bHoney Bottles&r have a 30% chance"
		"- Feeding a bee a &bHoney Bucket&r will give an 80% chance, as well as putting nearby Bees into &alove mode&r, and fully heal the targeted bee. If the targeted bee is a baby, it has a chance of &agrowing up immediately&r."
		"- &bRoyal Jelly&r - either bottle or bucket - will fully heal the &eBee&r, age up a Baby one, and gives a 100% chance of &bProtection of the Hive&r."
	]
